      <p> Analysis of Canada’s Foreign Trade and the Prospect of the Sino-Canadian</p>
      <p> Trade Development</p>
      <p> GUAN Xiao－hong 1， SHAO Yun－yi 2</p>
      <p> （1. School of International Trade and Economics, Guangdong University of Foreign Studies,</p>
      <p> Guangzhou, Guangdong, 510420 ）</p>
      <p> ( 2. International Business School, Sun Yat-sen University, Zhuhai, Guangdong, 519082 )</p>
      <p> Abstract: Canada is among the most developed industrialized countries in the world and the most important coun-tries in international trade. The trade between China and Canada has been developing at high speed recent years. In 2007,the volume of trade between these two countries reached $30.38 billion, with growing range of economic cooperation anddiversifying composition of trade. This paper will do a research in depth focusing on the prospect of the trade betweenChina and Canada by means of analyzing the features of Canada’s foreign trade and the general situation of Sino-Canadiantrade, evaluating competitiveness for major commercial goods of these two countries, illustrating the impact of financial crisison Sino―Canadian trade development.</p>
      <p> Key words: Sino-Canadian trade; Competitiveness of trade; Composition of trade; Factor endowment divergence</p>
